566JSTypeConversions::JSTypeConversions(Structure* structure, JSDOMGlobalObject& globalObject, Ref<TypeConversions>&& impl)

569}
570
571void JSTypeConversions::finishCreation(VM& vm)
572{
573 Base::finishCreation(vm);
574 ASSERT(inherits(vm, info()));
575
576 static_assert(!std::is_base_of<ActiveDOMObject, TypeConversions>::value, "Interface is not marked as [ActiveDOMObject] even though implementation class subclasses ActiveDOMObject.");
577
578}

1837
1838JSC::IsoSubspace* JSTypeConversions::subspaceForImpl(JSC::VM& vm)
1839{
1840 auto& clientData = *static_cast<JSVMClientData*>(vm.clientData);
1841 auto& spaces = clientData.subspaces();
1842 if (auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForTypeConversions.get())
1843 return space;
1844 static_assert(std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSTypeConversions> || !JSTypeConversions::needsDestruction);
1845 if constexpr (std::is_base_of_v<JSC::JSDestructibleObject, JSTypeConversions>)
1846 spaces.m_subspaceForTypeConversions = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.destructibleObjectHeapCellType.get(), JSTypeConversions);
1847 else
1848 spaces.m_subspaceForTypeConversions = makeUnique<IsoSubspace> ISO_SUBSPACE_INIT(vm.heap, vm.cellHeapCellType.get(), JSTypeConversions);
1849 auto* space = spaces.m_subspaceForTypeConversions.get();
1850IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("unreachable-code")
1851IGNORE_WARNINGS_BEGIN("tautological-compare")
1852 void (*myVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSTypeConversions::visitOutputConstraints;
1853 void (*jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)(JSC::JSCell*, JSC::SlotVisitor&) = JSC::JSCell::visitOutputConstraints;
1854 if (myVisitOutputConstraint != jsCellVisitOutputConstraint)
1855 clientData.outputConstraintSpaces().append(space);
1856IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1857IGNORE_WARNINGS_END
1858 return space;
1859}
1860
1861void JSTypeConversions::analyzeHeap(JSCell* cell, HeapAnalyzer& analyzer)
1862{
1863 auto* thisObject = jsCast<JSTypeConversions*>(cell);
1864 analyzer.setWrappedObjectForCell(cell, &thisObject->wrapped());
1865 if (thisObject->scriptExecutionContext())
1866 analyzer.setLabelForCell(cell, "url " + thisObject->scriptExecutionContext()->url().string());
1867 Base::analyzeHeap(cell, analyzer);
1868}

1872 UNUSED_PARAM(handle);

1878void JSTypeConversionsOwner::finalize(JSC::Handle<JSC::Unknown> handle, void* context)
1879{
1880 auto* jsTypeConversions = static_cast<JSTypeConversions*>(handle.slot()->asCell());
1881 auto& world = *static_cast<DOMWrapperWorld*>(context);
1882 uncacheWrapper(world, &jsTypeConversions->wrapped(), jsTypeConversions);
1883}

1885JSC::JSValue toJSNewlyCreated(JSC::JSGlobalObject*, JSDOMGlobalObject* globalObject, Ref<TypeConversions>&& impl)
1886{
1887 // If you hit this failure the interface definition has the ImplementationLacksVTable
1888 // attribute. You should remove that attribute. If the class has subclasses
1889 // that may be passed through this toJS() function you should use the SkipVTableValidation
1890 // attribute to TypeConversions.
1891 static_assert(!std::is_polymorphic<TypeConversions>::value, "TypeConversions is polymorphic but the IDL claims it is not");
1892 return createWrapper<TypeConversions>(globalObject, WTFMove(impl));
1893}

1896{
1897 return wrap(lexicalGlobalObject, globalObject, impl);
1898}
